==English==

===Etymology 1===
Latin: ''fons'': fountain.

====Alternative spellings====
*[[fount]]

====Noun====
'''font'''  (''plural:'' '''[[fonts]]''')
# A [[fountain]].
# A receptacle in a church for holy water - especially one used in [[baptism]]
# A receptacle for oil in a lamp.

===Etymology 2===
Old French ''[[fondre]]'': to melt.

====Noun====
'''font'''  (''plural:'' '''[[fonts]]''')
# A grouping of consistently designed [[glyph]]s, usually intended for use in [[typeset]]ting.
# A computer file encapsulating such a grouping, usually consisting of an association of glyphs to [[byte]]s or [[Unicode]] code points, and providing the glyphs as either precomposed [[bitmap]]s, or instructions for drawing the glyphs as a set of [[vector]]s and [[Bezier curve]]s, plus additional [[hint]]s and rendering guidance for different situations.

